data.description: Modern and energy-efficient, this newer home built in 2016 boasts 13 solar panels, which will be fully owned at close of escrow. Nestled on a corner lot within a cul-de-sac, this home features a convenient bedroom and full bath on the main floor.  Its proximity to the beach and military bases makes it an ideal location.  The spacious gourmet kitchen showcases white cabinets, granite counter tops, and stainless-steel appliances.  With laminate flooring throughout the lower level, window coverings, and ceiling fans, this house offers both style and comfort.  A large glass sliding door opens to a wooden deck in the backyard, perfect for outdoor entertaining. The front yard requires minimal maintenance with artificial turf, while the complex includes a small park and BBQ area. Did I mention water softener?  Yes, there is one! Enjoy the convenience of a short bike ride to the beach and nature preserve, and easy access to the nearby I-5 freeway.
